## 7. Pull Request Requirements

### 7.1 PR Template

**.github/pull_request_template.md:**
```markdown
## Description

[Describe what this PR does]

## Type of Change

- [ ] Bug fix
- [ ] New feature
- [ ] Refactoring
- [ ] Documentation update
- [ ] Dependency update

## Checklist

- [ ] Tests pass locally (`npm run validate`)
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors
- [ ] ESLint shows no warnings
- [ ] Code is formatted with Prettier
- [ ] New features have tests
- [ ] Accessibility tested (VoiceOver/TalkBack if UI changes)
- [ ] GraphQL codegen is up to date
- [ ] No console.log statements in committed code
- [ ] Environment variables documented (if added)

## Testing

[Describe how this was tested]

## Screenshots (if UI changes)

[Add screenshots]

## Related Issues

Closes #[issue number]
```

**Enforces:**
- Checklist completion
- Testing description
- Issue linkage

---

### 7.2 Automated PR Checks

**GitHub Actions can add:**
- **Bundle size check** (warn if bundle grows >10%)
- **Dependency review** (block PRs with vulnerable deps)
- **Label enforcement** (require `feature`, `bug`, or `docs` label)

